cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper discusses the analysis of scientific publications in high-energy physics, which involves a significant amount of digital library research (cs.DL). The study also involves the use of data mining and information retrieval techniques to assign authors to countries (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the geographical collaborative patterns of the HEP community (cs.SI), and the possible transition of HEP publishing to an Open Access model (cs.CY). Finally, the paper provides information on the journals favoured by the HEP community (cs.SD).
